# fcitx5 is the input method on the KDE targets only (Fedora KDE Spin, Ubuntu
# Studio); GNOME hosts (Fedora Workstation, Ubuntu Desktop) stay on GNOME's
# default ibus stack, so neither the fcitx5 config nor the fcitx XMODIFIERS
# environment drop-in may deploy there — a stray XMODIFIERS=@im=fcitx would
# point XWayland apps at an input method that isn't running. Detection mirrors
# the solaar rules template: GNOME-only means gnome-shell on PATH without
# plasmashell; with neither desktop (headless, container, CI) the files keep
# deploying as before.
{{- if and (eq .chezmoi.os "linux") (lookPath "gnome-shell") (not (lookPath "plasmashell")) }}
environment.d/50-input-method.conf
fcitx5
{{- end }}

